{
  "doc_id": "3962",
  "text": "Recombinant Inbred Lines (RILs) are very useful in QTL analysis as they represent unique combinations of parental genotypes, and being immortal, they can be used for the analysis of many traits in many environments [CITATION_1] . During the production of RILs, there are additional opportunities for recombination during the selfing generations, compared to simple F 2 populations. A further improvement is the advanced intercross approach, in which beginning with the F 1 or F 2 generation, individuals are randomly intercrossed, thus increasing the opportunity of recombination before genotypes are fixed upon selfing [CITATION_2] .",
